agent.text: To file a Civil Harassment Restraining Order in Sacramento Superior Court, you need to complete the Request for Civil Harassment Restraining Order (Step 1) Packet (CV\E-CH-01) and present the completed forms to the Civil Front Counter - Window 14 in Room 102 of the Gordon D. Schaber Sacramento County Courthouse. You will need to pay a filing fee, but if you cannot afford it, you can request a fee waiver. After filing, if your forms are completed and filed by 11:30 a.m., you will receive your Order at 4:00 p.m. the same day. If the forms are filed after 11:30 a.m., then the Order will be ready for pick up after 4:00 p.m. the next court business day. It is your responsibility to have the respondent personally served no later than five (5) days prior to the scheduled hearing date. Proof of service for the respondent must be filed with the court prior to or at the time of the Civil Harassment Restraining Order hearing.

contexts.text:
Civil Harassment Restraining Orders: Sacramento Superior Court

Request to Modify / Terminate Civil Harassment Restraining Order: Instructions on Service (Step 2) Packet (CV\E-CH-06)

Filing Fee

 	You will be required to pay a 
	filing fee when you file your forms with the court. Acceptable payment types: Check,
 	Cash, Cashier's Check, Money Order, and 
	Credit Card (Visa and MasterCard). If you are unable to pay the filing fee, you may request
 	a 
	fee waiver.

 	If the Request for a Civil Harassment Restraining Order is based on a credible threat of violence or
 	stalking, the filing fee may be waived by the Judge.

Where do I file my forms?

 	Present completed forms to the Civil Front Counter - Window 14 in Room 102 of the 
	Gordon D. Schaber Sacramento County Courthouse, 720 9th Street, Sacramento, CA
 	95814. The hours of operation are 8:30 a.m. to 4:00 p.m., Monday through Friday.

 	One (1) original and one (1) copy of all documents are required at the time of filing.

 	For more information and the necessary forms, see the 
 	Request for Civil Harassment Restraining Order (Step 1) Packet (CV\E-CH-01).

When will I get my order?

 	If your forms are completed and filed by 11:30 a.m. you will receive your Order at 4:00 
 p.m. the same day. If the forms are filed after 11:30 a.m., then the Order will be
 ready for pick up after 4:00 p.m. the next court business day. The forms will be
 returned to you in the 1st Floor Lobby outside of Room 102 at the 
	Gordon D. Schaber Sacramento County Courthouse. In most cases, a hearing will be set
	within 21 days for you and the other party.

	It is the responsibility of the petitioner to have the respondent personally served
	no later than five (5) days prior to the scheduled hearing date. Proof of service
	for the respondent must be filed with the court prior to or at the time of the
	Civil Harassment Restraining Order hearing.

|user|: How can I get a restraining order without notifying the other person of my address?
|assistant|: Unfortunately, I do not have information on how to keep your address confidential from the person you are seeking the restraining order against.
|user|: How do I file an order?
|assistant|: The procedure to file a restraining order depends on the type of restraining order and the court you want to file it in.
|user|: I am in Sacramento.
|assistant|: In Sacramento, you would file a restraining order at the Sacramento Superior Court. The specific steps for filing a restraining order can vary depending on the type of order you need.
|user|: What types of orders are there?
|assistant|: There are several types of restraining orders in Sacramento Superior Court, including Emergency Protective Order, Domestic Violence Restraining Order, Elder or Dependent Adult Abuse Restraining Order, Civil Harassment Restraining Order, Firearms Restraining Order, and Workplace Violence Restraining Order. Each has its own eligibility requirements and procedures.

After filing, if your forms are completed and filed by 11:30 a.m., you will receive your Order at 4:00 p.m. the same day.
